I can’t think of a better gift than the gift of technological advancements to help manage type 1 diabetes.  My boys have been using the FreeStyle Libre 2 flash glucose monitoring system* for two years now and it has helped our family immensely. Let me tell you, nothing is better than not having to do a routine finger poke** every time they need a glucose level reading, especially during all the seasonal festivities. With optional alerts that let us know if they are running dangerously high or low, anytime of the day or night, we are ready to enjoy the holidays stress free! Now that’s the perfect gift.
To learn more about the FreeStyle Libre 2 system, visit myfreestyle.ca. @FreeStyleDiabetes @AbbottGlobal #ad #TeamFreeStyleLibre
* The FreeStyle Libre 2 flash glucose monitoring system is indicated for measuring interstitial fluid glucose levels in people aged 4 years and older with diabetes mellitus. Always read and follow the label/insert.
**Finger pricks are required if readings do not match symptoms or expectations.

My boys are incredibly active. Throw Type 1 diabetes into that mix and some days are a full-blown circus. We love that we are in the know about their diabetes while on the go, using Abbott’s Freestyle Libre 2 system*. Whether they are out with friends, training at the gym or gearing up for the next big game, the Freestyle Libre 2 gives them the freedom to be active while keeping track of their glucose levels.
 
The system provides automatic alarms** to notify them when their glucose levels are out of range, or they can easily scan their sensor with their phone*** for a quick read on their glucose levels. We also have access to daily graphs of how their levels are trending which makes it easy for us to help them pinpoint what changes they need to make during busy days or high intensity sports. As a boy mom, Type 1 mom and hockey mom, that’s all the peace of mind I need to help manage their diabetes.
 
To learn more about the FreeStyle Libre 2 system, visit myfreestyle.ca. @FreeStyleDiabetes @AbbottGlobal #ad #TeamFreeStyleLibre
 
#type1diabetes #diabetescanada #type1mom #t1d #t1dlookslikeme #saskatchewan #yxe #saskhealth #momlife #myboys #freestylelibre
 
* The FreeStyle Libre 2 flash glucose monitoring system is indicated for measuring interstitial fluid glucose levels in people aged 4 years and older with diabetes mellitus. Always read and follow the label/insert.
**The FreeStyle Libre 2 system has optional glucose alarms. Alarms need to be turned on in order to receive low and high glucose alarms.
***The FreeStyle Libre 2 app is only compatible with certain mobile devices and operating systems. Please check the website for more information about device compatibility before using the app.

I’ve seen some new faces around here so wanted to take a second to say, “hi” and reintroduce myself. 👋🏼 

I am Andrea, a busy mom of 3 boys. I’m originally from Toronto, On. but settled down in the prairies with my Sask born hubby. 🌾 

My full time occupation truly is a full time pancreas and second to that I love fashion and styling ladies on the side. I have a little bit of a jewelry obsession…..you’ll see. 

Here’s some kooky facts about me… Peanut butter and ketchup on toast is life!!! Yeah, you read that right. Oh, here’s a neat one - I’ve actually had my tonsils out twice. I’ve lived in Canada and Europe. I’m like Mr. T, you’d need to knock me out to get me on a plane. I’m a carb counting ninja as most days I’m knee deep in blood sugars and insulin doses. My husband used to play for my favourite hockey team, Toronto Maple Leafs. I couldn’t imagine being anything else than a boy mom. I also have a golden retriever named Grizz.  One day I hope my husband and I can retire in the desert.  Unpopular opinion, Ice cream is the worst and Taylor Swift is the best. ✌🏼 
.

Pool days with diabetes …. but make it simple. 🌊 💉 🩸
 
Before the Freestyle Libre 2*: Total mama worry and uncertainty, which meant constant finger pokes to monitor my boys’ glucose levels during a day at the pool.
With the Freestyle Libre 2: No worries or routine finger pricks**, just fun. We have the freedom of knowing we will get an alert*** to our phones if their glucose levels go out of range.
 
Ok, so pool days used to be a complete nightmare for me. When the boys swim, we unhook their insulin pumps. Which means they’re getting no insulin. So, I worry about high glucose levels. However, with all the energy they are working off swimming, I also worry about lows. It’s a fine line, I never know which way they will go, and these days it can be tough to navigate. Now, no more worries. The kids can easily scan**** their sensor from their smart phones to see where their glucose levels are. We also know their alarms will go off if their glucose levels go out of range so we can treat lows or highs before it becomes a big problem, which just lets us get back into the swim of things!
 
To learn more about the FreeStyle Libre 2 system, visit myfreestyle.ca. @FreeStyleDiabetes @AbbottGlobal #ad #TeamFreeStyleLibre
 
#type1diabetes #diabetescanada #type1mom #t1d #t1dlookslikeme #saskatchewan #yxe #saskhealth #momlife #myboys #freestylelibre
 
* The FreeStyle Libre 2 flash glucose monitoring system is indicated for measuring interstitial fluid glucose levels in people aged 4 years and older with diabetes mellitus. Always read and follow the label/insert.
**Finger pricks are required if readings do not match symptoms or expectations.
***The FreeStyle Libre 2 system has optional glucose alarms. Alarms need to be turned on in order to receive low and high glucose alarms.
****The FreeStyle Libre 2 app is only compatible with certain mobile devices and operating systems. Please check the website for more information about device compatibility before using the app.

Sensor is water-resistant in up to 1 metre (3 feet) of water. Do not immerse longer than 30 minutes.

My new favourite word – Automatic
We are so excited to announce the N E W features to Abbott’s FreeStyle Libre 2 flash glucose monitoring system*. With the new update, you can now automatically** receive your glucose readings directly to your smart phone, w•i•t•h•o•u•t scanning the sensor. I’m just a little excited! This new feature will allow the boys to manage their glucose levels with a quick glance of their FreeStyle Libre 2 app.***
You read that right, as long as they’re connected to Bluetooth, they won’t have to scan every time they want to see their glucose levels. Their glucose readings will automatically update on the app*** every minute. Not only will this help my boys during their classes, tests, workouts or when they are shredding up the hockey ice this season – but as their caregiver, their real-time readings are now sent automatically to the LibreLinkUp app****. Whether I’m in the stands cheering them on or in another room while they’re sleeping at night, I can now see where their levels are without having to scan. Now, all I have to do is open my app and have a quick look. Such a game changer! Just when I thought I had enough peace of mind .... I was given even more.
.
To learn more about the FreeStyle Libre 2 system, visit myfreestyle.ca. @FreeStyleDiabetes @AbbottGlobal #ad #TeamFreeStyleLibre
#type1diabetes #diabetescanada #type1mom #t1d #t1dlookslikeme #saskatchewan #yxe #saskhealth #momlife #myboys #freestylelibre

**Glucose readings are automatically displayed in the FreeStyle Libre 2 app only when the smartphone and sensor are connected and in range.
***The FreeStyle Libre 2 app is only compatible with certain mobile devices and operating systems. Please check the website for more information about device compatibility before using the app. ****The LibreLinkUp app is only compatible with certain mobile devices and operating systems. November, Diabetes Awareness Month, holds deep significance for my family. When Ryder was diagnosed with Type 1 diabetes at two years old, it was the scariest moment of my life. In an instant, everything changed, and I thought the future I had envisioned for my boy would be over. I worried that he would never play sports, go trick-or-treating, or even drink a Slurpee. However, when my second son, Logan, was diagnosed at the age of five, I found myself in a different mindset. Over time, I learned that through planning, proper insulin dosing, and having the right tools, my boys can play sports, enjoy treats and experience a happy and healthy childhood.
Being introduced to the FreeStyle Libre 2* was a complete game changer. It’s more than just a device— it’s a tool that makes our lives easier. The FreeStyle Libre 2 app** sends real-time alerts*** to let us know when the boys are out of their proper glucose level range and allows us to see patterns to help us make any necessary health adjustments...which is extremely helpful as my boys are very active and are now carb-craving teenagers!
For parents of newly diagnosed kids, what I want you to know is that with the right tools and proper diabetes management, your children will thrive. Nothing has to change. My number one rule as a Type 1 mom is: kids first, diabetes second.
To learn more about the FreeStyle Libre 2 system, visit myfreestyle.ca. @FreeStyleDiabetes @AbbottGlobal #ad #TeamFreeStyleLibre

** The FreeStyle Libre 2 app is only compatible with certain mobile devices and operating systems. Please check the website for more information about device compatibility before using the app. Use of FreeStyle Libre 2 may require registration with LibreView.
